<title>EL SALVADOR: Cinemark to jointly invest $35 mln in Centam.</title>
<headline>Cinemark to jointly invest $35 mln in Centam.</headline>
<dateline>SAN SALVADOR 1997-01-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>A joint venture between a U.S. and a Salvadoran company has earmarked $35 million to equip 100 movie theatres in Central America by the year 2000, a company director told Reuters.</p>
<p>&quot;We are revolutionizing the concept of movie theaters in the region,&quot; said Coralia Schonenberg, marketing director of Inversiones Bolivar, a Salvadoran company that will jointly invest with U.S.-based Cinemark International.</p>
<p>The first phase of the investment plan entailed $3.5 million for building 23 theatres in El Salvador and Costa Rica, Schonenberg said, with plans to invest later in Nicaragua and Honduras.</p>
<p>((San Salvador newsroom, +503-223-4746))</p>
